                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39s1m54q/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>stopped long since to send him the “Occid.”<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. S. I. Meyer &amp; Co</persName> have only paid $6.00, as<lb/> you'll\n                perceive, as they say it were possible<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. A. Jacobs</persName> their partner, residing in <placeName>New<lb/>\n                    York</placeName> may have paid their subscription dues<lb/> therefore please let\n                me know in relation<lb/> to it. You will otherwise notice, that<lb/> collections are\n                made very slowly; people<lb/> here do not like to pay. &amp; in reference<lb/> to\n                getting subscriptions to the contemplated<lb/> translations, I have been\n                unsuccessful.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Dr. Eckman</persName> has requested me to<lb/> ask you the\n                amt. Of his dues to the Occi-<lb/>dent; wishing to pay the same.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The President of the Congregation<lb/> “Emanu-El” has also desired\n                me to<lb/> inform you to send the Bill for the adver-<lb/>tisement of the ministry\n                of this congregation<lb/> for payment.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am truly sorry, that you find<lb/> cause of so much complaint\n                against <del>your</del><lb/> the course of your religious opponents. Though<lb/> to\n                advise you would for me be out of<lb/> place, yet as a true friend I take the<lb/>\n                liberty to remark, that whilst I do deeply<lb/> sympathize with your arduous duties\n                in battling<lb/> against such a bitter opposition, &amp; whilst your<lb/> course is\n                applauded still by a large multi-<lb/>tude, it being a noble &amp; honorable\n                one,</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p39s1m54q/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
